    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Bite from iguana",
        "Often involves upper extremities or face"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Etiologies"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Microbiology of iguana oral flora poorly characterized",
        "Salmonella sp. has been transmitted by handling iguanas and lizards",
        "Infections reported due to Staphylococcus aureus and Serratia marcescens",
        "Case report of bullous cellulitis due to S. marcescens."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Primary Regimens"
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Optimal regimens not defined. Would choose agent that covers possible skin flora of victim (Staph and Strep) and well as Gram-negative bacteria, including Salmonella sp. from lizard:"
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Amoxicillin-clavulanate",
                "dose": "875/125 mg",
                "route": "po",
                "frequency": "twice daily"
              },
              {
                "connector": "+",
                "drug": "Ciprofloxacin",
                "dose": "750 mg",
                "route": "po",
                "frequency": "twice daily"
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Alternative Regimens"
    },
    {
      "type": "drugRegimen",
      "regimenData": {
        "strengthOfRecommendation": "Alternative",
        "components": [
          {
            "drug": "Piperacillin-tazobactam",
            "dose": "4.5 gm",
            "route": "IV",
            "frequency": "q8h",
            "notes": "(over 4 hr)"
          },
          {
            "connector": "or",
            "drug": "Imipenem"
          },
          {
            "connector": "or",
            "drug": "Meropenem"
          },
          {
            "connector": "or",
            "drug": "Cefepime"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Anti-staphylococcal agent + agent likely to be active against Serratia and other Enterobacteriaceae such as Gentamicin.",
        "Trimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole possible alternative to a fluoroquinolone"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Comments"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Administer tetanus toxoid or Tdap (preferred) if > 10 years since last dose",
        "Review of animal bite wounds (Clin Microbiol Rev 24: 231, 2011)"
      ]
    }
  ]
